{{Use mdy dates|date=April 2012}} {{Infobox organization | name = Accounting and Finance Association of Australia and New Zealand | named_after = | image = | image_size = | alt = | caption = | logo = | logo_size = | logo_alt = | logo_caption = | map = | map_size = | map_alt = | map_caption = | map2 = | map2_size = | map2_alt = | map2_caption = | abbreviation = | motto = | predecessor = | merged = | successor = | formation = 1960<!-- use {{start date and age|YYYY|MM|DD}} --> | founder = | founding_location = | extinction = <!-- use {{end date and age|YYYY|MM|DD}} --> | merger = | type = Association | tax_id = <!-- or | vat_id = (for European organizations) --> | registration_id = <!-- for non-profit org --> | status = | purpose = | headquarters = | location = | coords = <!-- {{coord|LAT|LON|display=inline, title}} --> | region = | services = | products = | methods = | fields = | membership = | membership_year = | language = | owner = <!-- or | owners = --> | sec_gen = | leader_title = | leader_name = | leader_title2 = | leader_name2 = | leader_title3 = | leader_name3 = | leader_title4 = | leader_name4 = | board_of_directors = | key_people = | main_organ = | parent_organization = | subsidiaries = | secessions = | affiliations = | budget = | budget_year = | revenue = | revenue_year = | disbursements = | expenses = | expenses_year = | endowment = | staff = | staff_year = | volunteers = | volunteers_year = | slogan = | mission = | website = <!-- {{URL|example.com}} --> | remarks = | formerly = | footnotes = }} '''Accounting and Finance Association of Australia and New Zealand''' ('''AFAANZ''') is an incorporated not-for-profit organization that was established in 2002 by the Accounting Association of Australia and New Zealand (AAANZ) and the Australian Association of University Teachers in Accounting (AAUTA).<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Y1OsDAAAQBAJ&pg=PT175&lpg=PT175&dq=When+was+AFAANZA+formed?&source=bl&ots=-dbfec-o6N&sig=hfHQJI8U6LdL4bkZYuTWO6hvi4E&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwj5ypeJtojXAhXHwVQKHSwOA4UQ6AEIKTAA#v=onepage&q=new%20zealand&f=false|title=A Dictionary of Accounting|last=Law|first=Jonathan|date=2016-09-22|publisher=Oxford University Press|isbn=9780191061172|language=en}}</ref> This organization represents the academic interests of people interested in accounting or finance, and helps develop new research to improve in this field in the Australian and New Zealand region.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.afaanz.org/background |work=Accounting and Finance Association of Australia and New Zealand |title=AFAANZ's Main Page |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160425142322/http://www.afaanz.org/background |archivedate=April 25, 2016 }}</ref>
AFAANZ hosts an annual conference in early July in various locations throughout the region. In 2018 the conference will be held in Auckland, New Zealand.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.afaanz.org/conferences|title=Conferences|last=2021admin|website=www.afaanz.org|language=en-gb|access-date=2017-10-24}}</ref>
Individual or institutional memberships are available. Individual memberships can help people earn benefits and scholarships.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.afaanz.org/memberships/afaanz-membership|title=Individual Membership|last=2021admin|website=www.afaanz.org|language=en-gb|access-date=2017-10-24}}</ref> Institutional memberships help reinforce connections between AFAANZ and universities.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.afaanz.org/memberships/institutional-membership|title=Institutional Membership|last=2021admin|website=www.afaanz.org|language=en-gb|access-date=2017-10-24}}</ref>
Any AFAANZ member can have access to the AFAANZ newsletter, which is published quarterly, in March, June, September and December.
