'''Barry Tannenbaum''' (born 1966) is a [[South Africa]]n businessman who was accused of the largest corporate fraud in South Africa.<ref>{{cite news | first=Nick | last=O'Malley | first2=Thomas | last2=Graham | title=Exposed: the Sydney man accused of $1.5 billion scam | url=http://www.smh.com.au/national/exposed-the-sydney-man-accused-of-15-billion-scam-20090612-c640.html | work=[[The Sydney Morning Herald]] | date=June 13, 2009}}</ref>
==Biography== Tannenbaum was born in [[Johannesburg]] in 1966.
In 2007, he moved to [[Sydney]].<ref name=taxi/>
In 2009, he was accused of running a [[South African rand|R]]10 billion [[Ponzi scheme]] in the largest corporate fraud in South Africa. The fraud promised 880 investors returns of 200% per year in investments related to pharmaceutical imports.<ref>{{cite news | first=Rebecca | last=Harrison | title=S.Africa fraud worth up to $1.2 billion uncovered |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/safrica-fraud/update-3-s-africa-fraud-worth-up-to-1-2-billion-uncovered-idUSLBO2543820090611 | work=[[Reuters]] | date=June 11, 2009}}</ref> However, South Africa never issued a formal [[extradition]] request.<ref name=taxi/>
In February 2015, he was an [[Uber]] driver in [[Runaway Bay, Queensland]].<ref name=taxi>{{cite news | url=https://www.news24.com/SouthAfrica/News/SA-Ponzi-boss-Tannenbaums-new-life-as-a-taxi-driver-20150208 | title=SA Ponzi boss Tannenbaum's new life as a taxi driver | work=[[News24]] | date=February 8, 2015}}</ref>
