{{Infobox football biography | name = Fred Blankemeijer | fullname = Fredrik Klaas Blankemeijer | image = | birth_date = {{birth date|1926|8|13|df=y}} | birth_place = [[Rotterdam]], [[Netherlands]] | death_date = {{death date and age|2010|11|8|1926|8|13|df=y}} | death_place = [[Rotterdam]], [[Netherlands]] | height = {{height|m=2.00|precision=0}} | position = [[Defender (association football)|Defender]] | youthyears1 = | youthclubs1 = | years1 = 1949–1952 | clubs1 = [[Feyenoord Rotterdam|Feijenoord]] | caps1 = 28 | goals1 = 0 | nationalyears1 = | nationalteam1 = | nationalcaps1 = | nationalgoals1 = | manageryears1 = | managerclubs1 = [[Feyenoord]] (youth coach) | manageryears2 = | managerclubs2 = [[Feyenoord]] (scout) | manageryears3 = | managerclubs3 = [[Feyenoord]] (board member) | manageryears4 = | managerclubs4 = [[Feyenoord]] (technical director) }}
'''Fred Blankemeijer''' (13 August 1926 – 8 November 2010) was a [[Netherlands|Dutch]] footballer who was active as a defender. A one-club man, he was member of Feijenoord for over 70 years.
==Club career== A tall but skinny defender, Blankemeijer made his professional debut at [[Feyenoord Rotterdam|Feijenoord]], and played a total of 28 matches for the club between 1949 and 1953.<ref>[https://www.feyenoord.nl/nieuws/nieuwsoverzicht/55026 Fred Blankemeijer 1926-2010] - Feyenoord {{nl|icon}}</ref>
==Retirement== After his career he would serve the club for many years in many occupations.<ref>[http://www.vi.nl/nieuws/fred-blankemeijer-het-geweten-van-feyenoord.htm?channel=phone Fred Blankemeijer, het geweten van Feyenoord] - Voetbal International {{nl|icon}}</ref> He was a youth coach, a scout, a board member as well as a technical director. He was decorated Knight of the [[Order of Orange-Nassau]] in 2004.<ref>[http://www.vi.nl/nieuws/blankemeijer-in-ere-hersteld-bij-feyenoord.htm?channel=phone Blankemeijer in ere hersteld bij Feyenoord] - Voetbal International {{nl|icon}}</ref> In June 2010 he served Feyenoord for a total of 70 years.
Widely regarded as a real club icon, he died of pneumonia, aged 84, on 8 November 2010.<ref>[http://www.ad.nl/ad/nl/1429/Feyenoord/article/detail/530458/2010/11/08/Feyenoord-icoon-Blankemeijer-overleden.dhtml Vlaggen bij Kuip halfstok na overlijden Blankemeijer] – AD {{nl|icon}}</ref>
